 herrather dreadful parents asked to see my books (as a suspicious physicianmight ask for a sample of semen), she gave them to read by mistake anotherman's novel because of a silly similarity of titles. The only real shock Iexperienced was when I overheard her informing some idiot woman friend thatmy Dare included biographies of "Chernolyubov and Dobroshevski"! Sheactually started to argue when I retorted that only a lunatic would havechosen a pair of third-rate publicists to write about--spoone